content:
The OmniScript Matrix Action enables you to retrieve a value from a calculation matrix by specifying required input parameters. 

For example, the matrix specifies insurance premiums based on age, sex and smoking status. The OmniScript collects user data, submits it to the matrix, and displays the resulting premium.

The Matrix Input Parameters field maps data from the Data JSON to the parameters that the matrix defines. Choose the matrix from the Remote Options dropdown list and enter a DateTime value in the Execution Date Time field to control when the matrix executes.
title: Understanding OmniScript Matrix Actions
